### Q2. What conditions cause `init_dkvt` to return without `vram_union_block`?

`src/llama-kv-cache-dkvt.cpp` L264–278 — every early return leaves `vram_union_block = nullptr`:

```cpp
void llama_kv_cache::init_dkvt(size_t n_ubatch, ggml_backend_sched_t sched) {
    if (vram_union_block) return;        // ① already initialized
    if (!sched)          return;        // ② scheduler null

    bool has_transcodable = false;
    for (...) {
        if ((is_transcodable_type(orig_type) && EXT flag)) { has_transcodable=true; break; }
    }
    if (!has_transcodable) return;      // ③ no EXT-flagged turbo layer

    if (n_seq_max > 1) throw(...);      // ④ n_seq_max>1 → hard error (speculative/decode not supported)

    if (other) { init_dkvt_borrow(); return; }  // ⑤ companion context — borrows from parent

    // ... compute union_size, find backend, alloc ...
    if (!init_dkvt_find_backend(sched, buft, buffer_id)) return;  // ⑥ no GPU backend found
    if (!init_dkvt_alloc(buft)) return;     // ⑦ allocation failed → no union block
```

| Condition | State | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| `vram_union_block != nullptr` | `PlainAllocated` → already bound | Safe re-entry guard |
| `!sched` | PlainAllocated | Scheduler missing → impossible in normal flow |
| `!has_transcodable` | PlainAllocated | Layers lack EXT flag or turbo type → no DKVT needed |
| `n_seq_max > 1` | **throws** | DKVT single-session only |
| `other != nullptr` | companion borrows parent union block | Valid state — union block set via `init_dkvt_borrow` |
| `!init_dkvt_find_backend` | PlainAllocated | No GPU backend in scheduler → return, no GPU buffer |
| `!init_dkvt_alloc` | **PlainAllocated** | Allocation failed → `vram_union_block` stays null |
| `union_size=0` (no layers) | PlainAllocated | `init_dkvt_sum_kv_sizes()` computes 0; `init_dkvt_alloc` won't set block |

**Root cause of PP↔TG degeneracy** — `src/llama-kv-cache-transcode.cpp` L239–283:
```cpp
void llama_kv_cache::transcode_to_tg(void * stream) {
    if (!vram_union_block || !ptr_start) return;  // early return if never allocated
    if (is_transcoded_tg) return;                 // already done — idempotent

    if (other) {
        if (other->is_transcoded_tg) { v_trans=true; dkvt_bind_tg(); is_transcoded_tg=true; }
        return;                                   // companion sync path
    }
    // ... CUDA or CPU transcode ...
    v_trans = true;
    is_transcoded_tg = true;
}
```

If `init_dkvt` hit condition ③, ⑥, or ⑦ above, `transcode_to_tg` silently returns without touching `v_trans` or `is_transcoded_tg`. The graph then sees stale PP layout — attention reads K/V at wrong offset → repeated `/`.

