### Q3. After `transcode_to_tg` what sets `v_trans` and tensor types for attention?

`transcode_to_tg` is the **only** place that sets `v_trans` and `is_transcoded_tg` to `true`:

| Location | Line | Action |
|---|---|---|
| `src/llama-kv-cache-transcode.cpp` L282 | post-transcode | `v_trans = true; is_transcoded_tg = true;` |
| `src/llama-kv-cache-transcode.cpp` L247–249 | companion path | `v_trans=true; dkvt_bind_tg(); is_transcoded_tg=true;` |

**Tensor type rewiring** happens inside `dkvt_bind_tg()` called *before* those flags are set:

`src/llama-kv-cache-dkvt.cpp` L60–107 — `dkvt_bind_tg()`:
```cpp
void llama_kv_cache::dkvt_bind_tg() {
    for each layer i:
        ggml_type target_type_k = dkvt_tg_type_k(layers[i].orig_type_k);  // turbo→F16
        ggml_type target_type_v = dkvt_tg_type_v(layers[i].orig_type_v);  // turbo→Q8_0

        if (EXT flag) {
            layers[i].k->data = ptr_start + size_act_tg + dkvt_v_size_tg + k_offset_tg;
            layers[i].v->data = ptr_start + size_act_tg + v_offset_tg;
            dkvt_update_strides(layers[i].k, target_type_k);   // rewrites .type, .nb[]
            dkvt_update_strides(layers[i].v, target_type_v);
        }
    // also updates stream tensors with target types
}
```

`dkvt_update_strides` (`src/llama-kv-cache-dkvt.h` L21–26) directly mutates `tensor->type`, `tensor->nb[0..3]`:
```cpp
