int64_t kv_size     = v_trans ? layers[i].v->ne[0] : layers[i].v->ne[1];
```

`v_trans=true` means V layout `[kv_size, head_size_v, n_head_kv, n_ctx]` (kv_size in dim 0); `v_trans=false` means `[head_size_v, kv_size, n_head_kv, n_ctx]`. After `transcode_to_tg`, `v_trans` is **always** set to `true` regardless of the original `orig_v_trans`. This is the mandatory TG layout — without it, V head_size and kv_size are swapped and attention reads garbage → repeated token output.

